task.summary: Default task
Fixed CORS issue
Changed schema to support non-int course numbers, and fixed bugs with downloading script regarding missing lectures, non-int course numbers, & course names with slashes.
Added API endpoints (and APIClient.js functions) to search for professors, departments, & quarters. Also added some minimal tests for these additional auxiliary API functions.
Added API endpoint & client function for checking if a user has favorited a podcast.
Added id field to podcasts returned by getFavorites()
Added API endpoints + tests (and front-end API Client functions) to send password token email & set a new password for the user.

Update podcast transcripts API to also return the full transcript split into sections of sentences, so that the front-end can easily render the full-transcript broken up into paragraphs, to improve readability.
Dockerized backend for easy setup & usage (and updated backend README instructions to follow Docker)
Refractored API keys into a .env file and removed the Sendgrid API key from the code.
Fixed bug in APIClient's getPodcastTranscript function.

Updated download_podcast_data.py script to download videos & convert them to audio (while skipping podcasts without video or audio). Also, made it multi-threading, so it finishes the bulk task of downloading all of a course's converted podcast audios in ~10 minutes.
Added temporary offset files to be used for importing the podcast transcription data. This is a temporary fix while we re-transcribe the podcasts with the video's audio track.
Fixed buggy forgot-password API endpoints and API client functions.
Added forgot password functionality
Some minor refractors
Dockerized the entire MVP (backend, frontend, elasticsearch)
Updated front-end docker setting to enable live reload during development.
Added transcriptions for Chem 4 F18 and CSE 141 F18
Updated search API endpoints in order to return all possible values for departments, quarters, and professors when no query is specified.
Added .env file to .gitignore
Added API endpoint to get all available course codes.
Removed dot.env file from repo. Pls do not commit to the repo with this file, in order to prevent the API key from getting deactivated.
Updated docker configuration for front-end.
Changed front-end app's nginx port
Added production docker-compose file.
Updated dockerfile for frontend to include build
Updated autocomplete functions, and fixed history API
Updated dockerfiles & README to resolve some of the issues with installation.
Updated README
Fixed saved input query/filter values across searches.
Changed PodcastPage.js to just use the blob_id url parameter.
Changed history page to add links to previous search queries (+ including the saved filters of the particular search) and course podcasts.
Fixed history page layouting issues and made favorites page linked.
Updated docker-compose version to 3.6

Updated History page layout, and fixed some bugs in ResSearch.js and filtering (quarter now filters by exact match). In order to run this version, database data should be cleared & a fresh rebuild is needed.
Updated history page.
Ran npm build.
Slightly changed backend's Dockerfile to try to make it wait for elasticsearch before starting/exiting/and looping this process for a couple times, before ES is actually up and running.
Updated README with some docker instructions/tips
Fixed backend crashing during startup
Ran npm build
Updated production docker-compose file.
Updated favorites page to align the stars and titles.
Updated favorites page to align the stars and titles.
Added an empty state screen to the history page and the favorites page.
inflating my commits with npm build
Fixed history page bug
Fixed logout popup glitch, added script for importing test users, and updated README for info about the script for importing test users (one fresh user and one populated user).

Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/master'
